-- Obama to talk about auto industry at noon
-- 
-- Thu Apr 30, 2009 11:25am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/30/us-autos-obama-sb-idUSTRE53T3W920090430

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - U.S. President Barack Obama will deliver remarks on the U.S. auto industry at 12 p.m. EDT (1600 GMT) on Thursday, the White House said in a statement. 

 The statement said he would be joined at the White House by members of his autos task force.